05701nam a22007335i 9783110790955DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20222022gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97831107909557 a10.1515/97831107909552doi  a(DE-B1597)624023  a(OCoLC)1347246462  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aART0000002bisacsh02aA General History of Chinese Art. nVolume 3, pA General History of Chinese Art ; Sui and Tang Dynasties /ced. by Xifan Li. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2022] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (XII, 442 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aA General History of Chinese Art ;vVolume 300tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tOVERVIEW -- tCHAPTER I SPECTACULAR COURT MUSIC AND DANCE OF THE SUI AND TANG DYNASTIES -- tCHAPTER II MUSIC AND DANCE OF THE PREFECTURES, COUNTIES, DEFENSE COMMANDS AND THE LITERATI; RICH DIVERSITY IN FOLK MUSIC, DANCE AND VARIETY SHOWS -- tCHAPTER III THE GLORY OF THE ART OF DANCE -- tCHAPTER IV BRILLIANT ACHIEVEMENTS IN THE MUSICAL ARTS -- tCHAPTER V THE ACHIEVEMENTS AND DEVELOPMENT OF OTHER IMPORTANT VARIETY ARTS -- tCHAPTER VI THEORIES OF THE PERFORMING ART IN THE SUI AND TANG DYNASTIES AND EXCHANGES IN MUSIC, DANCE, AND VARIETY SHOWS -- tCHAPTER VII THE ART OF CALLIGRAPHY IN THE SUI AND THE EARLY TANG -- tCHAPTER VIII THE ART OF CALLIGRAPHY IN THE HIGH, MIDDLE, AND LATE TANG -- tCHAPTER IX PAINTINGS AND MURALS OF THE SUI AND TANG DYNASTIES -- tCHAPTER X SCULPTURAL ART OF THE SUI AND TANG DYNASTIES -- tCHAPTER XI ARCHITECTURE AND CRAFT ARTS OF THE SUI AND TANG DYNASTIES -- tCHAPTER XII MATURATION AND ACHIEVEMENTS OF SUI AND TANG THEORIES OF CALLIGRAPHY AND PAINTING0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDieser Band untersucht die Entwicklung chinesischer Kunst während der Sui- und Tang-Dynastie, unter deren Herrschaft die verschiedenen Disziplinen der bildenden und darstellenden Künste eine Phase beispielloser Entwicklung erlebten. Darüber hinaus werden neue Entdeckungen in der Kalligraphie, Malerei und Wandmalerei sowie architektonische Errungenschaften beleuchtet. A General History of Chinese Art umfasst sechs Bände mit insgesamt neun Teilen, die von der prähistorischen Ära bis zum 3. Jahr von Xuantong während der Qing-Dynastie (1911) reichen. Das Werk bietet eine umfassende Zusammenstellung eingehender Studien über die Entwicklung chinesischer Kunst während der Regierungszeiten der jeweiligen Dynastien und untersucht die Entstehung eines breiten Spektrums künstlerischer Kategorien wie Musik, Tanz, Akrobatik, Gesang, Malerei, Kalligrafie, Skulptur, Architektur und Kunsthandwerk. Im Gegensatz zu früheren Referenzwerken bietet A General History of Chinese Art einen breiten Überblick über den Begriff der chinesischen Kunst, indem es von einem vielfältigen und weniger materiellen Verständnis von Kunst ausgeht, wie meist von der westlichen Wissenschaft vertreten.  aThis volume covers Chinese art during the reign of the Sui and Tang Dynasties during which the various disciplines of plastic and performing arts all entered a stage of unprecedented prosperity and development. It also traces new explorations in calligraphy, painting, and mural art and highlights architectural achievements during the historic period. A General History of Chinese Art comprises six volumes with a total of nine parts spanning from the Prehistoric Era until the 3rd year of Xuantong during the Qing Dynasty (1911). The work provides a comprehensive compilation of in-depth studies of the development of art throughout the subsequent reign of Chinese dynasties and explores the emergence of a wide range of artistic categories such as but not limited to music, dance, acrobatics, singing, story telling, painting, calligraphy, sculpture, architecture, and crafts. Unlike previous reference books, A General History of Chinese Art offers a broader overview of the notion of Chinese art by asserting a more diverse and less material understanding of arts, as has often been the case in Western scholarship.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aArchitektur. 4aBildhauerei. 4aKalligraphie. 4aKunst. 4aMalerei. 4aMusik. 4aPerformance. 4aSuidynastie. 4aTangdynastie. 4aTanz. 7aART / General.2bisacsh  aChina.  aIntroduction.  aSui and Tang Dynasties.  aarchitecture.  aart.  acalligraphy.  adance.  amusic.  apainting.  aperformance.  asculpture.1 aLi, Xifan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt0 cprintz978311078929440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311079095540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110790955423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110790955/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles